---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"
import SectionTitle from "../components/SectionTitle.astro"

const blockClasses =
  "flex flex-col gap-3 border-b border-neutralTech-200 dark:border-neutralTech-800 pb-8"

const titleClasses =
  "text-h3 font-semibold text-brand-wine dark:text-brand-beige transition-colors duration-base"

const paragraphClasses =
  "text-body text-neutralTech-700 dark:text-neutralTech-200 transition-colors duration-base"

const linkClasses =
  "text-brand-wineMuted dark:text-neutralTech-200 hover:text-brand-wine dark:hover:text-brand-beige transition-colors duration-base text-body font-medium"
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects">
  <main 
    class="py-paddingPage flex flex-col items-center gap-12"
    data-testid="projects-page"
  >

    <!-- Header -->
    <div 
      class="w-full max-w-4xl text-center"
      data-testid="projects-header"
    >
      <SectionTitle 
        class="items-center text-center [&>h2]:text-h1"
        title="Projects"
        subtitle="A curated and technical overview of the systems, tools, and products I’ve engineered"
        data-testid="projects-title"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- Project List -->
    <section class="w-full max-w-4xl flex flex-col gap-12">

      <!-- PROJECT 1 -->
      <section 
        class={blockClasses} 
        aria-labelledby="project-portfolio"
        data-testid="projects-section-1"
      >
        <h2 
          id="project-portfolio" 
          class={titleClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-1-title"
        >
          1. Portfolio Website
        </h2>

        <a 
          href="https://github.com/andradeg-luiza/andradeg-luiza"
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class={linkClasses}
          aria-label="Explore the Portfolio Website project"
          data-testid="projects-section-1-link"
        >
          Explore this project →
        </a>

        <p 
          class={paragraphClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-1-text"
        >
          A fully engineered personal platform built with Astro, TypeScript, and TailwindCSS, designed to showcase technical expertise, projects, and long‑term engineering direction. 
          The system follows a modular architecture optimized for performance, accessibility, and maintainability. 
          It includes unit tests (Vitest) and end‑to‑end tests (Playwright), ensuring reliability across components and user flows. 
          CI/CD pipelines via GitHub Actions automate testing, linting, building, and deployment to GitHub Pages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- PROJECT 2 -->
      <section 
        class={blockClasses} 
        aria-labelledby="project-focusflow"
        data-testid="projects-section-2"
      >
        <h2 
          id="project-focusflow" 
          class={titleClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-2-title"
        >
          2. FocusFlow — Productivity & Workflow System
        </h2>

        <a 
          href="https://github.com/andradeg-luiza/focusflow"
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class={linkClasses}
          aria-label="Explore the FocusFlow project"
          data-testid="projects-section-2-link"
        >
          Explore this project →
        </a>

        <p 
          class={paragraphClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-2-text"
        >
          FocusFlow is a structured productivity system designed to improve execution, prioritization, and workflow clarity. 
          Built with a strong engineering mindset, it applies principles of task orchestration, modular architecture, and maintainable code design. 
          The project reflects deep understanding of state management, UI/UX for productivity tools, and automation‑driven workflows.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- PROJECT 3 -->
      <section 
        class={blockClasses} 
        aria-labelledby="project-autoapplybot"
        data-testid="projects-section-3"
      >
        <h2 
          id="project-autoapplybot" 
          class={titleClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-3-title"
        >
          3. Auto Apply Bot — Automated Job Application Tool
        </h2>

        <a 
          href="https://github.com/andradeg-luiza/autoapplybot"
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class={linkClasses}
          aria-label="Explore the Auto Apply Bot project"
          data-testid="projects-section-3-link"
        >
          Explore this project →
        </a>

        <p 
          class={paragraphClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-3-text"
        >
          An automation tool designed to streamline job application workflows by interacting with job platforms programmatically. 
          The bot automates repetitive tasks such as form filling, data extraction, and structured submissions. 
          Built with Node.js, automation scripts, and robust error handling, it showcases strong skills in browser automation, workflow optimization, API interaction, and reliability engineering.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- PROJECT 4 -->
      <section 
        class={blockClasses} 
        aria-labelledby="project-donna"
        data-testid="projects-section-4"
      >
        <h2 
          id="project-donna" 
          class={titleClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-4-title"
        >
          4. Donna — Engineering Assistant
        </h2>

        <a 
          href="https://github.com/andradeg-luiza/donna"
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class={linkClasses}
          aria-label="Explore the Donna project"
          data-testid="projects-section-4-link"
        >
          Explore this project →
        </a>

        <p 
          class={paragraphClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-4-text"
        >
          Donna is an AI‑powered engineering assistant focused on automation, documentation, and workflow optimization. 
          It integrates structured logic, modular services, and automation routines to support engineering tasks such as generating documentation, organizing workflows, and assisting with testing processes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- PROJECT 5 -->
      <section 
        class="flex flex-col gap-3" 
        aria-labelledby="project-qakb"
        data-testid="projects-section-5"
      >
        <h2 
          id="project-qakb" 
          class={titleClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-5-title"
        >
          5. QA Knowledge Base
        </h2>

        <a 
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/andradegluiza/"
          target="_blank" 
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class={linkClasses}
          aria-label="Explore the QA Knowledge Base project"
          data-testid="projects-section-5-link"
        >
          Explore this project →
        </a>

        <p 
          class={paragraphClasses}
          data-testid="projects-section-5-text"
        >
          A comprehensive and evolving knowledge base documenting QA methodologies, automation strategies, testing patterns, engineering workflows, and best practices. 
          It consolidates insights from 16+ years of experience across support, QA, automation, and SDET roles.
        </p>
      </section>

    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
